episodes.title: The Note
episodes.plot: Physical therapy proves painful for Jerry when his small talk with the therapist leads to a misunderstanding; Jerry uses a dentist note to cover his therapy.

episodes.title: The Truth
episodes.plot: A bad breakup between George and his girlfriend leads to tax troubles for Jerry.

episodes.title: The Pen
episodes.plot: Jerry and Elaine travel to Florida for a dinner in honor of his father. Jerry gets into an argument with a neighbor of his parents over an "astronaut pen."

episodes.title: The Dog
episodes.plot: Jerry is forced to care for the disobedient dog of a man he met on a plane.

episodes.title: The Library
episodes.plot: The library asks Jerry about a book he checked out in 1971 and never returned, so Jerry looks up an old girlfriend for his defense against a library cop.

episodes.title: The Parking Garage
episodes.plot: The four get stuck in a parking garage for hours when they forget where they parked.

episodes.title: The Cafe
episodes.plot: Jerry tries to help a new immigrant restaurant owner across the street from him. George, afraid of embarrassment, asks Elaine to take an IQ test for him.

episodes.title: The Tape
episodes.plot: George orders hair growing cream from China. Jerry is mesmerized by a dirty message left on a tape recorder from his last performance. George becomes infatuated with Elaine.

episodes.title: The Nose Job
episodes.plot: Jerry dates a vacuous actress and struggles with overcoming his sexual desire for her. George dates a woman with a large nose, who decides to get a nose job after a careless comment from Kramer.

episodes.title: The Stranded
episodes.plot: Jerry and Elaine join George for a special party, where they send signals to each other to get out of bad party conversations; George had an office romance.

episodes.title: The Alternate Side
episodes.plot: Jerry's car is stolen. Elaine dates an older man. Kramer gets a small role in a Woody Allen movie filmed on his and Jerry's block. George must deal with the commotion of the movie filming as he gets a job parking cars on the block.

episodes.title: The Red Dot
episodes.plot: George gets a job at Elaine's office and gets involved with the cleaning woman. Elaine's boyfriend is a recovering alcoholic who falls off the wagon because of Jerry's carelessness. George buys Elaine a marked-down cashmere sweater.

episodes.title: The Subway
episodes.plot: Everyone has an uncommon experience while going their separate ways on the subway; Kramer overheard a hot tip on a horse on his way to pay a traffic violation.

episodes.title: The Pez Dispenser
episodes.plot: Jerry's Pez dispenser makes Elaine laugh during George's girlfriend's piano recital and puts their relationship in jeopardy; Kramer joins the Polar Bear Club.

episodes.title: The Suicide
episodes.plot: After a suicide attempt by Jerry's neighbor lands him in a coma, Jerry begins a relationship with his girlfriend. George visits a psychic who predicts trouble on his upcoming trip. Elaine agonizes over having to fast before surgery.

episodes.title: The Fix Up
episodes.plot: Against their better judgment, Jerry and Elaine decide to play matchmaker for the jobless, dateless and possibly hopeless George, setting him up with a single friend of Elaine's.

episodes.title: The Boyfriend
episodes.plot: Elaine and Keith are hitting it off until he pulls out a cigarette; Keith wants Jerry to help him move, leading Jerry along with Elaine to breakup with Keith.

episodes.title: The Limo
episodes.plot: Jerry and George take a limo from a passenger that Jerry knows never made it on the plane, but their false identities land them in hot water.

episodes.title: The Good Samaritan
episodes.plot: Jerry dates a woman who sideswiped a car, then learns the victim is someone he wants to date. George is drawn into Robin and Michael's marital problems when he says "Bless you" after Robin sneezes. Kramer has mysterious seizures.

episodes.title: The Letter
episodes.plot: Jerry learns that his new artist friend, from whom George has been forced to buy a painting, plagiarized a letter to keep him from breaking up with her. Elaine refuses to remove her Baltimore Orioles cap during a New York Yankees game.

episodes.title: The Parking Space
episodes.plot: Coming from an outing to a flea market in Westchester, Elaine and George damage Jerry's car when George drives over a large pothole. When they get to his apartment they conveniently find a parking space right in front of Jerry's building. As George tries to back in however, someone tries to take the spot by driving in nose-first. Neither car is able to park, and an all-day argument ensues.. Meanwhile, Elaine must come up with a story about the damage to the car.

episodes.title: The Keys
episodes.plot: Jerry is fed up with Kramer's coming into his apartment any time he feels like it and asks him to return his spare set of keys. Kramer begrudgingly complies but then lets it be known that he's leaving for California. As for the others, the one key swap leads to multiple exchanges on pretty well everyone's part. When Jerry forgets his keys, he gets George to let him into Elaine's apartment so he can get his spare set. What they find interests them.
